Paper: hep-th/9705074

Date: 1997-05-12

Title: Anomalous Creation of Branes

Authors: Constantin Bachas, Michael R. Douglas and Michael B. Green

Comments: 7 pages, two figures

Journal-ref: JHEP 9707 (1997) 002

In certain circumstances when two branes pass through each other a thirdbrane is produced stretching between them. We explain this phenomenon by theuse of chains of dualities and the inflow of charge that is required for theabsence of chiral gauge anomalies when pairs of D-branes intersect.